node.text:
If you missed us while we were live, head to my IGTV to watch the full video. Don’t forget that you will need: 
1. A comb
2. Scissors •• (buy good ones NOT kitchen scissors!) 3. Hair clips or ties for sectioning.
4. A cape or garbage bag! 
Send us a before and after of your hair cut so we can see how you did. Tag me and @riawna when you post! Good luck!!!!

node.text: You can never be too cautious. Don’t just wash your hands, wash the groceries when you come back from the store. Hope you are too! • Inspired by @dakotajohnson •

node.text: A few months ago, we filmed this and if only I knew then what I know now. “The only constant in life is change.” Those words have never rung more true. We’re living through a very unique moment in history, with a lot of change and turbulence. Every day is a new challenge, with ups and downs and I’m doing my best to embrace all this gracefully. I’m really trying. And I have to remind myself that the only thing I can control at this moment is me, how I feel and how I react to things. That doesn’t mean it’s easy, but I’m looking for daily silver linings. Reading a lot. Cooking. Working on my mental health. Connecting with loved ones over FaceTime. Picking up new hobbies at home. Doing my best to adapt. I hope you are too. Stay strong everyone. This too shall [eventually] pass. How will you grow from this experience? @dior
